<TITLE> Jalil leaves for Singapore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 3 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil left for Singapore for medical treatment, accompanied by his wife, shortly before Monday midnight, an airport official said. Security had been tightened in and around Zia International Airport ahead of Jalil's flight to the city-state. The AL leader"critically" ill with heart and kidney ailmentswas released on one-month parole with a series of conditions attached. Khandaker Rafiqul Islam, deputy police commissioner for Uttara Zone, told bdnews24.com that more than 150 police personnel had been deployed at the airport. The Rapid Action Battalion and other security agencies mounted watch in the area to avert what the police officer said was any untoward incident. The police also tightened security around the house of Jalil's Gulshan home where he had gone from LabAid Cardiac Hospital to spend some time with his family, en route to airport. Earlier in 1979, ASM Abdur Rab, president of Jatiya Samajtantrik Dal (Rab), who was convicted in a case, was sent to Germany for medical treatment. Jail authorities do not have records on how Rab was released and sent to Germany for treatment, IG (prisons) Md Zakir Hasan told bdnews24.com. bdnews
